          Comparator<User> nameDescComparator = Comparator.comparing(User::getName).reversed();

          Chaining Comparators:
              One of the most powerful features of the Java 8 Comparator is the ability to chain sorting logic. 
              For example, if two users have the same age, you might want to sort them by name.
               List<User> users = ...;
               users.sort(
                   Comparator.comparingInt(User::getAge)
                             .thenComparing(User::getName)
               );

