Custom Checked Exception
  A custom checked exception extends Exception (but not RuntimeException).
Key Characteristics:
  Checked at compile time
  Must be handled using try-catch OR declared using throws
  Used for recoverable conditions

Custom Unchecked Exception
  A custom unchecked exception extends RuntimeException.
Key Characteristics:
  Not checked at compile time
  No mandatory handling
  Used for programming errors / bugs

Best Practices:
